      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "The weather conditions fostered a strengthening of the snowpack in particular on sunny slopes. Towards its surface, the snowpack is largely stable and its surface has a melt-freeze crust that is strong in many cases. <br/> 2 to 5 cm of snow, but less in some localities, fell on Monday above approximately 1600 m. Up to 15 cm in areas bordering Piedmont, with a quick settling in. <br/> Especially steep shady slopes high altitudes and the high Alpine regions: Weak layers exist in the old snowpack. Towards its surface, the snowpack consists of faceted crystals; its surface consists of faceted crystals. <br/> Adjacent to ridgelines and in pass areas as well as at high altitude snow depths vary greatly, depending on the infuence of the wind."
      },
